shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Understanding_person-centred_values_-_standard_5_care_certificate_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1692793155" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Understanding_person-centred_values_-_standard_5_care_certificate_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1692793155 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Understanding_person-centred_values_-_standard_5_care_certificate_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1692793155 320w" width="2000" height="1333" alt="Understanding person-centred values - standard 5 care certificate - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Understanding person-centred values - standard 5 care certificate - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-leSONj uTJGF pf-25_"/><p class="sc-dMOJrz cGFGtP pf-26_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-28_">The initial step in establishing a person-centred approach to care is to train the staff to comprehend person-centred values. This will be beneficial in guiding them on how to put these values into practice in their day-to-day work. By prioritising individual needs and preferences over routine procedures, staff learn to involve the person they care for and their families in decision-making processes, respect privacy, promote independence, and offer choices. Through needs-led care plans, staff learn to create personalised support guides that consider the preferences and wishes of the individuals they care for.<br><br>Person-centred care promotes independence, dignity, and respect while building a positive relationship between the person receiving support and the support provider. By training staff to embrace these values, they are empowered to make a meaningful impact on the lives of the individuals they support. Adhering to this standard also helps you meet the regulatory requirements of the Care Quality Commission (CQC) Regulation 9. This regulation specifies the necessary steps providers must take to ensure that each person receives appropriate person-centred care and treatment based on their needs and preferences.<br> </span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-jeraig eTNnJl pf-29_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-31_">Understand working in a person-centred way </span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Understand_working_in_a_person-centred_way_-_cater_certificate_training_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1692793253" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Understand_working_in_a_person-centred_way_-_cater_certificate_training_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1692793253 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Understand_working_in_a_person-centred_way_-_cater_certificate_training_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1692793253 320w" width="2240" height="1493" alt="Understand working in a person-centred way - cater certificate training - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Understand working in a person-centred way - cater certificate training - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-leSONj uTJGF pf-32_"/><p class="sc-dMOJrz cGFGtP pf-33_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-35_">Providing care that is tailored to the needs, preferences, and values of the individual is what it means to work in a person-centred way. By taking part in the train-the-trainer program, you will learn the necessary skills and knowledge to implement person-centred care practices. These practices include effective communication, active listening, and involving individuals and their families in decisions related to their care. The train-the-trainer program highlights the significance of collaboration and empowering individuals to make informed choices about their care. </span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-jeraig eTNnJl pf-36_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-38_">Demonstrate awareness of an individual's immediate environment</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Demonstrate_awareness_of_an_individual_s_immediate_environment_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1692793339" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Demonstrate_awareness_of_an_individual_s_immediate_environment_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1692793339 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Demonstrate_awareness_of_an_individual_s_immediate_environment_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1692793339 320w" width="2351" height="1610" alt="Demonstrate awareness of an individual's immediate environment - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Demonstrate awareness of an individual's immediate environment - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-leSONj uTJGF pf-39_"/><p class="sc-dMOJrz cGFGtP pf-40_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-42_">It's important to be aware of any potential environmental factors that could cause discomfort or distress to those you're caring for. By engaging in the train-the-trainer program, you'll learn how to conduct environmental assessments and identify any issues that may negatively affect someone's well-being. This could involve evaluating factors such as noise levels, lighting, and temperature. Addressing these concerns shows your dedication to creating a comfortable and supportive environment for individuals in your care.</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-jeraig eTNnJl pf-43_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-45_">Causing discomfort or distress</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Causing_discomfort_or_distress_-_Care_Certificate_Standard_5_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1692793438" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Causing_discomfort_or_distress_-_Care_Certificate_Standard_5_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1692793438 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Causing_discomfort_or_distress_-_Care_Certificate_Standard_5_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1692793438 320w" width="1920" height="1280" alt="Causing discomfort or distress - Care Certificate Standard 5 - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Causing discomfort or distress - Care Certificate Standard 5 - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-leSONj uTJGF pf-46_"/><p class="sc-bvFjSx yVjXo pf-47_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">In order to ensure the well-being of individuals receiving care, it is essential that staff members become aware of any actions they may be undertaking that are causing discomfort or distress. By participating in the train-the-trainer model, you will acquire the skills to facilitate open and honest communication within the care setting. Creating an environment where staff and individuals feel comfortable expressing their concerns is vital. This can involve providing feedback, encouraging reflection, and promoting a culture of continuous improvement.</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-jeraig eTNnJl pf-49_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-51_">Support individuals to minimise pain or discomfort</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Support_individuals_to_minimise_pain_or_discomfort_-_Standard_5_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1692793521" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Support_individuals_to_minimise_pain_or_discomfort_-_Standard_5_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1692793521 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Support_individuals_to_minimise_pain_or_discomfort_-_Standard_5_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1692793521 320w" width="2240" height="1493" alt="Support individuals to minimise pain or discomfort - Standard 5 - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Support individuals to minimise pain or discomfort - Standard 5 - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-leSONj uTJGF pf-52_"/><p class="sc-bvFjSx yVjXo pf-53_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Assisting people in handling pain or discomfort is an essential part of providing individual-focused care. By taking part in the train-the-trainer program, you will acquire skills and methods to help people effectively reduce pain or discomfort. This involves grasping the significance of prompt and appropriate pain management, implementing positioning techniques, and helping individuals access pertinent healthcare professionals or services.</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-jeraig eTNnJl pf-55_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-57_">Support the individual to maintain their identity and self-esteem</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Support_the_individual_to_maintain_their_identity_and_self-esteem_-_Care_Certificate_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1692793596" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Support_the_individual_to_maintain_their_identity_and_self-esteem_-_Care_Certificate_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1692793596 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Support_the_individual_to_maintain_their_identity_and_self-esteem_-_Care_Certificate_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1692793596 320w" width="2000" height="1333" alt="Support the individual to maintain their identity and self-esteem - Care Certificate - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Support the individual to maintain their identity and self-esteem - Care Certificate - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-leSONj uTJGF pf-58_"/><p class="sc-bvFjSx yVjXo pf-59_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Preserving the individual's identity and self-esteem is paramount to enhancing their well-being and ensuring a positive care experience. By participating in the <a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/products/care-certificate-standard-5-train-the-trainer-course-trainer-pack?variant=31848427946053" target="_blank"><i><span style="color: rgb(0, 102, 204);">Standard 5 Care Certificate train-the-trainer course and pack</span></i></a>, you will gain insight into the importance of treating individuals with respect, dignity, and empathy. Recognising and valuing individuality, cultural background, and personal preferences contributes to the self-esteem of those you care for.</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-jeraig eTNnJl pf-61_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-63_">Support using person-centred values</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Support_using_person-centred_values_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1692793687" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Support_using_person-centred_values_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1692793687 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Support_using_person-centred_values_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1692793687 320w" width="2371" height="1413" alt="Support using person-centred values - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Support using person-centred values - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-leSONj uTJGF pf-64_"/><p class="sc-bvFjSx yVjXo pf-65_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">By having a thorough grasp of person-centred values, you will be able to offer assistance that caters to each individual's specific requirements and preferences. You will learn how to apply the six person-centred values - dignity, respect, privacy, individuality, choice, and independence - in practical situations. This involves engaging the in